      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the world of real estate, where even the most mundane tasks can be as tricky as a goblin's riddle. Escrow, my friend, is like a magical goblin's vault where all the treasures (or in your case, money and documents) are kept safe until the grand finale, the house closing. It's a neutral ground, a safe haven, where neither the buyer nor the seller can sneak a peek until the deal is sealed. This way, both parties can be sure that the other is playing fair, just like a goblin ensuring no one steals his shiny trinkets. So, when your realtor mentions the escrow account, think of it as a goblin's treasure chest, holding onto your hard-earned gold until the house is finally yours.",
